$interpreted: Naya: Sione, we've found it! The missing tracks lead in this direction, OVER HERE!
Sione: Wait. Something doesn't feel right.
Naya: What's wrong? And what were you looking at?
Sione: This rune device belongs to the Sunshine Infantry.
Sione: It can detect specific rune markings, like the ones inside our missing rune chariot.
Naya: That's wonderful, then won't we be able to track down Angel?
Sione: It only works up to a certain distance. There's not even the slightest detection at present...
Sione: They had enough time to cover their tracks yet left them behind... feels like a decoy.
Naya: WHAT?! If we keep following these tracks, won't we wander straight into their trap?
Sione: Quick! Return to where the tracks end. Perhaps there are hidden clues we overlooked.
Naya: Mhm, move fast!
Sione: Resonance is strongest here. The rune chariot that took the princess must be nearby!
Naya: Dear Sione, look sharp!
Kidnapper: Have we been found?!
Naya: Damn it, bring Her Highness out!
Sione: ...The princess isn't here...
Kidnapper: Hmph. Our allies took her away long ago.
Naya: Where have they taken Angel to?! SPEAK!
Kidnapper: Uhh...uhh...uhhh...
Sione: ...Suicide...
Naya: Don't lose hope. We've already found the rune chariot.
Naya: They can run, but they can't hide. Sooner or later Angel will be found!
Sione: But the rune device could only locate the chariot. It won't aid us any further.
Naya: Then we'll start from this broken wagon, and spread out into the surroundings! Surely we'll find Angel, have some faith!

Sione: You're right... Angel must be waiting for us.
We cannot despair.
Naya: Exactly! I'll head in that direction!
Sione: I'm going this way, rendezvous here later.
